  "text": "To asses participants' ability to imagine motor acts, the Vividness of Movement Imagery Questionnaire (VMIQ) will be used [CITATION_1] . Individuals are required to rate the vividness of their imagery on a 5-point scale (1 = as perfectly clear and vivid as normal vision, 5 = no image at all -only a vague awareness of thinking about the movement) for 24 different movements from both an external (i.e. watching somebody else) and internal (doing it yourself) perspective. VMIQ scores have been linked to improvements in motor skills [CITATION_2] .",
